      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"marketplace of ideas\" theory posits that truth emerges organically from the free collision of all viewpoints, no matter how extreme. When governments impose \"safety\" regulations, they are effectively acting as gatekeepers, deciding which ideas are permissible and which must be suppressed. This governmental vetting process inevitably substitutes bureaucratic judgment for open debate, chilling legitimate dissent. Ultimately, allowing the state to define \"unsafe\" speech is the most direct path to authoritarian control over thought.",
